Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa says Health Minister Aaron Motsoaledi has been working vigorously to ensure all patients receive the right care. JOHANNESBURG - Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa says Health Minister Aaron Motsoaledi has been working vigorously to ensure all patients receive the right care in the wake of the Life Healthcare Esidimeni tragedy. More than 100 people died after being transferred from the Gauteng facility to several unlicensed non-governmental organisations (NGOs) last year.Health MEC Qedani Mahlangu resigned over the tragedy.Ramaphosa says government is taking steps to make sure the tragedy never repeats itself. Motsoaledi has his director general (Precious Matsoso) scouring throughout the length and breadth of the country to ensure that the tragedy doesn t happen in other provinces. The health minister also has his officials on their toes working on this matter. He says the minister is giving full attention to the matter. Let s give Motsoaledi all the help rather than criticising and browbeating him to the ground. The minister is doing a good job under very difficult circumstances. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)